<div id="review_1433493026" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1433493026" />
    <a title="➸ Gwen de Sade" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/13454735-gwen-de-sade"><img alt="➸ Gwen de Sade" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1633893174p2/13454735.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1433493026?book_show_action=true">Nov 04, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="➸ Gwen de Sade" class="user" itemprop="url" name="➸ Gwen de Sade" href="/user/show/13454735-gwen-de-sade">➸ Gwen de Sade</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9783518100493" href="/book/show/241114.Mutter_Courage_und_ihre_Kinder">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/13454735-gwen-de-sade?shelf=2016">2016</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/13454735-gwen-de-sade?shelf=classics">classics</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1433493026" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8144170020655237064">I read a lot of books this year with the same message: war is absurd, war destroys everything and afterwards, no one knows exactly what they were fighting for. I don&apos;t even know why I read so many books on the subject, I usually really don&apos;t like WWII or generally war literature, it just makes me deeply uncomfortable and depressive. I&apos;ve been avoiding Anne Frank for the last 5 years for example, although it is patiently sitting on my shelf.<br/><br/>However, once again, Brecht is different, different than</span>
  <span id="freeText8144170020655237064" style="display:none">I read a lot of books this year with the same message: war is absurd, war destroys everything and afterwards, no one knows exactly what they were fighting for. I don't even know why I read so many books on the subject, I usually really don't like WWII or generally war literature, it just makes me deeply uncomfortable and depressive. I've been avoiding Anne Frank for the last 5 years for example, although it is patiently sitting on my shelf.<br /><br />However, once again, Brecht is different, different than anything I ever read on the subject. He is such a genius, I don't even have words to describe him.<br /><br /><br />Full review to come as soon as I have a little time and I'm on my laptop.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8144170020655237064" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


