<div id="review_3810793000" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3810793000" />
    <a title="Ananya M" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/9613048-ananya-m"><img alt="Ananya M" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1642570059p2/9613048.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3810793000?book_show_action=true">Feb 02, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ananya M" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ananya M" href="/user/show/9613048-ananya-m">Ananya M</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9789384052379" href="/book/show/28946828-mother-courage-and-her-children">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3810793000" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer991523015419695090">This is my first time reading Brecht, I see the hype. This is a play in 12 scenes, following Anna, also known as mother courage, who sells wares from her cart, along with her 3 children. This is set during the thirty years war. Mother courage goes from town to town, lugging her cart and selling things to anyone in need. I appreciated how her character was not the definition of moral good, she wanted to take care of her kids by making sales, but when they hear a rumour that the war ended, she beg</span>
  <span id="freeText991523015419695090" style="display:none">This is my first time reading Brecht, I see the hype. This is a play in 12 scenes, following Anna, also known as mother courage, who sells wares from her cart, along with her 3 children. This is set during the thirty years war. Mother courage goes from town to town, lugging her cart and selling things to anyone in need. I appreciated how her character was not the definition of moral good, she wanted to take care of her kids by making sales, but when they hear a rumour that the war ended, she began to realize that she wanted war so she could sell things. There is this question of whether she is doing everything for her kids or if she’s doing it for the money. Did she get so accustomed to the war that peace now seems like a curse?<br />Her children die, one by one, leaving her all alone with nowhere to go and no one to go with. It’s a sad play, obviously because it’s set during a war, but also has some great lines about finding hope and peace even with war and destruction around. </span>
  <a data-text-id="991523015419695090" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


