<div id="review_4087759558" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4087759558" />
    <a title="Aditya Narayan" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/40927634-aditya-narayan"><img alt="Aditya Narayan" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1498637624p2/40927634.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4087759558?book_show_action=true">Jul 13, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Aditya Narayan" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Aditya Narayan" href="/user/show/40927634-aditya-narayan">Aditya Narayan</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4087759558" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4573642724093409735">This is a preciuos play. Although, I find it difficult to read text of a play because it has a lot of it&apos;s attributes in the execution of the play onstage. This is the first ever play by Brecht I have read and I&apos;ll tell you why I hadn&apos;t read him so far, I thought he is not a great talent because he is a communist. Yeah, I thought so because lots of people (anti-communists) said this to me. Yes, I know it&apos;s stupid and unfortunate and yet here we are. Anyway. <br/><br/>So, Brecht&apos;s motive in this play is ba</span>
  <span id="freeText4573642724093409735" style="display:none">This is a preciuos play. Although, I find it difficult to read text of a play because it has a lot of it's attributes in the execution of the play onstage. This is the first ever play by Brecht I have read and I'll tell you why I hadn't read him so far, I thought he is not a great talent because he is a communist. Yeah, I thought so because lots of people (anti-communists) said this to me. Yes, I know it's stupid and unfortunate and yet here we are. Anyway. <br /><br />So, Brecht's motive in this play is basically to portray how petite bourgeoisie benefits from war and other such atrocities to protect what he thinks is his very own and yet in the end nothing is left of him. He loses everything despite his mindless conformity. <br /><br />The plays takes place in times of 30 years of war of faith (between Catholics and Protestants) and displays it's the inhuman outcomes. That's it's novelistic quality. <br /><br />If we avoid going into the ideological debates of the play, it still counts as a classic for it's timeless portrayal of human life, it's struggles and tragedies of a war. This brief pocket sized book will leave an unforgettable imprint on anybody's mind who reads it. But also, it does put forward it's ideological view very clearly and convincingly. <br /><br />My first introduction to epic theatre and Brecht had been very impressive. Now, I'll be on hunt of some good staged plays available online. Let's see what do I get.<br /><br />The songs are unforgettable too and both the songs and the play requires revisit again and again.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4573642724093409735" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


